:: What is digital scholarship? {"position":"725,500","size":"100,100"}
An excellent question! 

**Digital scholarship** encompasses a wide range of digital methods‚Äîfrom digital mapping (GIS) to text mining to data visualization to 3D modeling‚Äîand emphasizes interdisciplinary and interdepartmental collaborations.

It is a broad category that includes, among many things:

* Public-facing scholarship
* Non-traditional publishing methods (alternatives to books and articles)
* Scholarship that uses computational tools borrowed from other disciplines
* Library- or collections-based research

Some think of it as an expansion of "digital humanities" to include more disciplines

[[But what is Digital Humanities?|dh]]

